  <description type="morphology">Herbs, annual or perennial (stems and leaves glabrous except 43. H. setosum); black glands absent. Leaves deciduous (base articulated) or persistent (base not articulated). Flowers 3–15 mm diam.; sepals persistent, (4–)5; petals persistent, (4–)5; stamens persistent, (5–)10–80, usually in continuous or interrupted ring, sometimes in 5 barely discernable fascicles, each of 1–2 stamens; ovary (2–)3(–4)-merous; placentation parietal; styles ± spreading, bases distinct; stigmas capitate or clavate. Seeds not carinate.</description>
